                            <comment id="17173" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Wed, 12 Apr 2006 05:03:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This was actually a deliberate change in behavior, although I tend to agree that breaking backwards compatibility is unpleasant here (even if it&apos;s simple enough to fix). Hence, I&apos;ve added the following special behavior: If the specified path is an absolute file path (according to the underlying operating system), we&apos;ll consider it as straight file path. Else it&apos;s gonna be parsed as Spring resource location (URL or relative file path). This should cover all typical cases, while being largely backwards-compatible (for absolute file paths, which is what typically got specified for a property of type java.io.File).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18648" author="jsolinsky" created="Tue, 18 Jul 2006 01:27:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As of RC-2, the fix descibed by Juergen has not been implemented. Does this mean that:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. The code has not been checked in?&lt;br/&gt;
2. A decision was made not to implement this or&lt;br/&gt;
3. Something else?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;JWS&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
